The evidence with the title 'Andrew Jackson | HistoryNet ' says On january 8, 1815, Jackson and his men rebuffed a British frontal assault at Chalmette Plantation outside New Orleans and won the battle , due in no small part to very bad luck on the part of the British .  ... In january 1835 , Jackson paid off the entire national debt , the only time in U.S. history that has been accomplished. 
